did.unittitle:
And Quiet Flows the Ganga.  People's Union
for Democratic Rights. New Delhi, People's Union for Democratic Rights,
India: 1983.

scopecontent.p:
Publications in this category cover a wide range of issues in education in
                     India, including: curriculum formation and syllabi; education planning;
                     illiteracy; teacher training; universities and colleges; rural education;
                     testing; adult education programs; and educational reform. Pamphlets also
                     discuss specific areas in education such as law, agricultural training,
                     religion, physical education, and science, to which an entire subgrouping is
                     devoted. The main subgroupings with further descriptions below are General
                     Education; Adult Education; Higher Education; Science Education; Syllabi;
                     Teacher Training; and Vocational Education. The two largest sections are
                     General Education, with 139 publications, and Higher Education, with 117.

The 142 pamphlets in this section were published by official government
                        agencies, private institutes, corporations and individuals from the 1960s to
                        the 1990s. They provide information on research and development in industry;
                        working conditions; heavy and medium to large size industries; the
                        development of industrial towns; companies such as Bhilai and Tatas; the
                        steel industry; textiles; chemicals; industrial training and education;
                        industrial finance; engineering; federal and state industrial policies;
                        promotional information; and industry in the public and private sectors.
                        There are also 25 publications by the Indian Standards Institution on the
                        Sectional List of Indian Standards.

The 158 pamphlets in this section were published by official government
                     agencies, NGOs and political parties. They touch on a wide variety of topics
                     relating to working conditions: labor conditions in various industries;
                     training; child labor; strikes and the right to strike; the constitutions and
                     rules and regulations of various trade unions; directories of trade union
                     leaders; discipline; domestic inquiries; collective bargaining; intervention
                     rivalries; All India Kisan Sabha; Hind Mazdoor Sabha; Bharatiya Mazdoor Sangh;
                     the Center for Indian Trade Unions; job statistics; and work benefits. Some
                     publications document meetings of various trade unions such as Indian National
                     Trade Union Congress (INTUC);

