scopecontent.p:
The 78 pamphlets in this section discuss a variety of topics concerning
                     education in Pakistan: government planning for education development; education
                     planning; syllabi; university calendars; exchange of scholars; federal spending
                     on educational planning; official and private educational institutions;
                     professional education; special education; primary and higher education;
                     illiteracy; adult education; People's Open University; vocational education;
                     and charts, graphs, and statistics on educational progress.

did.unittitle:
Hijacking Conspiracy against Pakistan and Ideology;
   Address to the Nation.  Zia-Ul-Haq, Mohammad. Islamabad, Ministry
